OL,3,CBurnham to propose 'a No 10 in the
OL,4,CNorth' in major speech
OL,6,FSenior Labour figures have insisted
OL,7,Fthe party is united behind the
OL,8,Fleadership frontrunner and dismissed
OL,9,Fthe prospect of a general election to
OL,10,Fsecure a mandate for any major shifts
OL,11,Fin policy.
OL,13,FHousing Secretary Steve Reed suggested
OL,14,FStarmer's likely successor would
OL,15,Fintroduce "changes in emphasis" but
OL,16,Fstick to the "fundamentals" such as
OL,17,Fthe government's rules on borrowing.
OL,26,@wD@KOUwD@_O]xD@NOUxD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
